# Bitazza iOS Architecture Proposal

## Executive Summary

After thorough analysis of the current ~95K-line codebase, I'm proposing a modular architecture using SPM local packages with clean layer separation, replacing Swinject with protocol-based constructor injection, and introducing a proper Coordinator pattern for SwiftUI navigation.

---

## 1. Module Strategy (SPM Local Packages)

### Module Graph

```
BitazzaApp (main target)
  ├── AppComposition       (DI root, coordinators, app lifecycle)
  │     ├── all feature modules
  │     └── DataLayer
  │
  ├── TradeFeature         (Trade screen, chart, order book)
  ├── WalletFeature        (Crypto/Fiat wallets, deposits, withdrawals)
  ├── MarketFeature        (Market lists, search, pair selection)
  ├── OnboardFeature       (Login, SignUp, PIN, Splash, Welcome)
  ├── DashboardFeature     (Dashboard, activities, KYC alerts)
  ├── SettingsFeature      (Settings, 2FA, security, referral)
  ├── OrdersFeature        (Open/completed orders, filters)
  ├── SpotFeature          (Buy/Sell limit/market/stop)
  ├── AddressBookFeature   (Address management, withdrawal success)
  ├── BTZRankFeature       (BTZ Rank, community scores)
  ├── AmityFeature         (Social feed, posts, profiles)
  │
  ├── DataLayer            (Repository implementations, networking, DTOs)
  │     ├── DomainLayer
  │     └── NetworkKit
  │
  ├── DomainLayer          (Entities, UseCase protocols, Repository protocols)
  │     └── (zero dependencies)
  │
  ├── NetworkKit           (Alamofire abstraction, WebSocket, interceptors)
  │
  ├── CoreUI               (Design system, shared SwiftUI components, styles)
  │     └── DomainLayer    (for shared entity types in UI)
  │
  └── SharedKit            (Extensions, utilities, keychain, analytics protocol)
```

### Dependency Rules

1. **DomainLayer** imports NOTHING (pure Swift, no frameworks). This is the inversion hub.
2. **NetworkKit** imports only Foundation + Alamofire + Starscream. No app types.
3. **DataLayer** imports DomainLayer + NetworkKit. Implements repository protocols.
4. **Feature modules** import DomainLayer + CoreUI + SharedKit. Never import DataLayer directly.
5. **AppComposition** (main app target) imports everything. This is the only place where concrete types are wired together.
6. Feature modules NEVER import each other. Cross-feature navigation goes through coordinator protocols defined in DomainLayer.

### Package.swift Example

```swift
// Package.swift (root of monorepo-style local packages)
let package = Package(
    name: "BitazzaModules",
    platforms: [.iOS(.v16)],
    products: [
        .library(name: "DomainLayer", targets: ["DomainLayer"]),
        .library(name: "DataLayer", targets: ["DataLayer"]),
        .library(name: "NetworkKit", targets: ["NetworkKit"]),
        .library(name: "CoreUI", targets: ["CoreUI"]),
        .library(name: "SharedKit", targets: ["SharedKit"]),
        .library(name: "TradeFeature", targets: ["TradeFeature"]),
        .library(name: "WalletFeature", targets: ["WalletFeature"]),
        // ... other features
    ],
    dependencies: [
        .package(url: "https://github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire.git", from: "5.9.0"),
        .package(url: "https://github.com/daltoniam/Starscream.git", from: "4.0.0"),
        .package(url: "https://github.com/onevcat/Kingfisher.git", from: "8.0.0"),
    ],
    targets: [
        .target(name: "DomainLayer", dependencies: []),
        .target(name: "SharedKit", dependencies: []),
        .target(name: "NetworkKit", dependencies: ["Alamofire", "Starscream"]),
        .target(name: "DataLayer", dependencies: ["DomainLayer", "NetworkKit"]),
        .target(name: "CoreUI", dependencies: ["DomainLayer", "SharedKit", "Kingfisher"]),
        .target(name: "TradeFeature", dependencies: ["DomainLayer", "CoreUI", "SharedKit"]),
        // ...
        .testTarget(name: "DomainLayerTests", dependencies: ["DomainLayer"]),
        .testTarget(name: "TradeFeatureTests", dependencies: ["TradeFeature"]),
    ]
)
```

---

## 2. Clean Architecture Layers

### DomainLayer

Pure Swift. No UIKit, no SwiftUI, no Combine (use async/await instead).

```swift
// MARK: - Entities (value types)

struct Instrument: Sendable, Equatable {
    let instrumentId: Int
    let product1Symbol: String
    let product2Symbol: String
    let priceDecimalPlaces: Int
    let quantityDecimalPlaces: Int
    var displayName: String { "\(product1Symbol)/\(product2Symbol)" }
}

struct OrderBook: Sendable, Equatable {
    let instrumentId: Int
    let side: OrderSide
    let price: Decimal
    let quantity: Decimal
    let updateId: Int
    let actionType: OrderBookAction
}

enum OrderSide: String, Sendable { case buy, sell }
enum OrderBookAction: Sendable { case new, update, deletion }

// MARK: - Repository Protocols (defined in Domain, implemented in Data)

protocol InstrumentRepository: Sendable {
    func getAllowedInstruments() async throws -> [Instrument]
    func getProducts() async throws -> [Product]
    func getLevel1Summary() async throws -> [Level1Summary]
}

protocol OrderBookRepository: Sendable {
    func subscribeLevel2(instrumentId: Int) -> AsyncThrowingStream<[OrderBook], Error>
    func unsubscribeLevel2(instrumentId: Int) async throws
}

protocol AuthRepository: Sendable {
    func login(username: String, password: String) async throws -> AuthResult
    func authenticate2FA(code: String) async throws -> Auth2FAResult
}

// MARK: - Use Cases

protocol GetAllowedInstrumentsUseCase: Sendable {
    func execute(forceUpdate: Bool) async throws -> [Instrument]
}

protocol SubscribeOrderBookUseCase: Sendable {
    func execute(instrumentId: Int) -> AsyncThrowingStream<[OrderBook], Error>
}

protocol LoginUseCase: Sendable {
    func execute(username: String, password: String) async throws -> AuthResult
}
```

**Key changes from current:**
- Replace `AnyPublisher<T, ApiError>` with `async throws` and `AsyncThrowingStream` for subscriptions
- Use value types (structs) instead of response models directly from network layer
- Repository protocols are Sendable for safe concurrent access
- No `BaseUseCase` class hierarchy -- each use case is a simple struct

### DataLayer

```swift
// MARK: - Repository Implementations

struct InstrumentRepositoryImpl: InstrumentRepository {
    private let networkService: NetworkService
    private let cache: InstrumentCache

    func getAllowedInstruments() async throws -> [Instrument] {
        if let cached = cache.instruments, !cache.isExpired {
            return cached
        }
        let dto: [InstrumentDTO] = try await networkService.request(
            .get("/instruments", query: ["status": "active"])
        )
        let instruments = dto.map { $0.toDomain() }
        cache.store(instruments)
        return instruments
    }
}

// MARK: - DTOs (Data Transfer Objects, separate from domain entities)

struct InstrumentDTO: Decodable {
    let InstrumentId: Int
    let Product1Symbol: String
    let Product2Symbol: String
    let PriceIncrement: Decimal
    let QuantityIncrement: Decimal

    func toDomain() -> Instrument {
        Instrument(
            instrumentId: InstrumentId,
            product1Symbol: Product1Symbol,
            product2Symbol: Product2Symbol,
            priceDecimalPlaces: PriceIncrement.significantFractionalDigits,
            quantityDecimalPlaces: QuantityIncrement.significantFractionalDigits
        )
    }
}
```

### Presentation Layer (inside Feature modules)

```swift
// Lives inside TradeFeature module
@Observable
final class TradeViewModel {
    // Dependencies (injected via init)
    private let getInstruments: any GetAllowedInstrumentsUseCase
    private let subscribeOrderBook: any SubscribeOrderBookUseCase
    private let coordinator: TradeCoordinator

    // State
    var selectedInstrument: Instrument?
    var orderBooks: [OrderBook] = []
    var latestPrice: String = "0.00"
    var isLoading = false
    var error: AppError?

    init(
        getInstruments: any GetAllowedInstrumentsUseCase,
        subscribeOrderBook: any SubscribeOrderBookUseCase,
        coordinator: TradeCoordinator
    ) {
        self.getInstruments = getInstruments
        self.subscribeOrderBook = subscribeOrderBook
        self.coordinator = coordinator
    }

    func onAppear() async {
        await loadInstruments()
    }

    func onBuyTap() {
        guard let instrument = selectedInstrument else { return }
        coordinator.showBuySell(productId: instrument.product1, side: .buy)
    }

    private func loadInstruments() async {
        isLoading = true
        defer { isLoading = false }
        do {
            let instruments = try await getInstruments.execute(forceUpdate: false)
            selectedInstrument = instruments.first
        } catch {
            self.error = AppError(from: error)
        }
    }
}
```

