## 3. Dependency Injection

Replace Swinject (8 files, complex runtime resolution, optional-heavy) with protocol-based constructor injection + a simple composition root.

### Current Problems
- `DependencyContainer.shared.resolve(T.self)!` -- force-unwrap throughout codebase
- `TradeViewModel.shared = DependencyContainer.shared.resolve(TradeViewModel.self)!` -- static singletons of ViewModels
- Runtime resolution errors only caught at crash time
- 7 Assembly files totaling hundreds of registrations

### New Approach: Factory Protocol + Composition Root

```swift
// MARK: - Factory Protocol (lives in DomainLayer)

protocol TradeFeatureFactory {
    func makeTradeViewModel() -> TradeViewModel
    func makeSpotBuySellViewModel(productId: Int, side: OrderSide) -> SpotBuySellViewModel
}

// MARK: - Composition Root (lives in AppComposition, main app target)

@MainActor
final class AppDependencyContainer {
    // Singletons for truly shared state
    private lazy var networkService = NetworkServiceImpl(
        baseURL: AppConfig.apiBaseURL,
        tokenProvider: { [weak self] in self?.sessionStore.accessToken }
    )
    private lazy var webSocketService = WebSocketServiceImpl(url: AppConfig.wsURL)
    private lazy var sessionStore = SessionStore()

    // Repositories
    private lazy var instrumentRepo = InstrumentRepositoryImpl(
        networkService: networkService,
        cache: InstrumentCache()
    )
    private lazy var authRepo = AuthRepositoryImpl(
        networkService: networkService,
        sessionStore: sessionStore
    )
}

extension AppDependencyContainer: TradeFeatureFactory {
    func makeTradeViewModel() -> TradeViewModel {
        TradeViewModel(
            getInstruments: GetAllowedInstrumentsUseCaseImpl(repo: instrumentRepo),
            subscribeOrderBook: SubscribeOrderBookUseCaseImpl(repo: orderBookRepo),
            coordinator: tradeCoordinator
        )
    }
}
```

**Benefits over Swinject:**
- Compile-time safety: missing dependencies are compiler errors, not runtime crashes
- No force-unwraps
- Easier to trace dependency graph
- Zero third-party dependency
- Each factory protocol can be mocked for tests

