## Key Design Decisions Summary

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Concurrency | async/await over Combine | Simpler, built-in, better error handling, no cancellable management |
| State | @Observable (iOS 17+) | Less boilerplate than ObservableObject, automatic dependency tracking |
| DI | Constructor injection + factory protocols | Compile-time safety, zero dependencies, easy testing |
| Navigation | Coordinator per feature | Decouples ViewModels from navigation, enables deep linking |
| Networking | Protocol abstraction over Alamofire | Testable, swappable, no framework leak into domain |
| Module system | SPM local packages | Fast builds, enforced boundaries, no CocoaPods for internal code |
| Error handling | Layered enums + ErrorPresenter | Type-safe, single presentation point, separates detection from display |
| CacheSession | Split into focused stores | Single-responsibility, observable, no god object |
| BaseViewModel | Eliminated | Composition over inheritance; error presentation via ErrorPresenter protocol |
| iOS minimum | iOS 16+ (17+ for @Observable) | @Observable is the architectural lynchpin; iOS 16 with ObservableObject fallback if needed |

